<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="134" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d134">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">851.51/6: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-15">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 15, 1914</hi>.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>159. Your No. 40, September 5th, also number 108, eleventh.<note n="1" xml:id="d134fn1">Latter not printed.</note> Inquiry has failed to
                            disclose any attempt to float French loan in this country. Press today
                            reports rumor that German loan of fifty millions is contemplated by
                            certain New York bankers. No confirmation of rumor.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>